---

<PageShell
  title="Japan Business Manager Visa 2026: Investment Requirements, Insurance & Application Guide"
  description="Complete guide to Japan's Business Manager Visa (経営・管理). ¥5,000,000 investment, company formation, mandatory NHI enrollment, and path to permanent residence."
  headline="Japan Business Manager Visa: Investment Guide"
  subheadline="Everything you need to know about Japan's Business Manager Visa—¥5,000,000 investment, company setup requirements, mandatory national health insurance, and building your business in one of the world's largest economies."
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Premium Insurance"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/allianz-care"
  heroImage="/images/countries/japan-hero-bg.png"
>

  <!-- Trust Signals -->
  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 mb-8 text-sm text-neutral-600">
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1">
      <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
      Updated February 2026
    </span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1">
      <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
      Official Japanese Requirements
    </span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1">
      <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
      ¥5,000,000 Investment Path
    </span>
  </div>

  <!-- Section: Overview -->
  <section id="overview" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Overview</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Japan's Business Manager Visa (経営・管理 / Keiei Kanri) allows foreign entrepreneurs and investors to establish and manage businesses in Japan. Unlike passive investment visas in other countries, Japan requires active business management—you must be genuinely running a company, not just providing capital. The minimum investment is ¥5,000,000 (approximately $33,000 USD), making it one of the more accessible entrepreneur visas globally.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Japan offers unique advantages: the world's third-largest economy, exceptional quality of life, remarkable safety, and access to Asian markets. The trade-off is Japan's business culture complexity, language barriers, and the requirement to actively manage your business. For entrepreneurs who embrace these challenges, Japan provides an extraordinary base for building a business.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts: Japan Business Manager Visa</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-primary-800">
        <li>• <strong>Official name:</strong> Business Manager Visa (経営・管理)</li>
        <li>• <strong>Minimum investment:</strong> ¥5,000,000 (~$33,000 USD)</li>
        <li>• <strong>Office requirement:</strong> Dedicated business premises (not home)</li>
        <li>• <strong>Duration:</strong> 1 year initial, renewable (3, 5 years possible)</li>
        <li>• <strong>Family included:</strong> Spouse and children (Dependent visa)</li>
        <li>• <strong>Path to PR:</strong> 10 years residence (or 1 year with HSFP points)</li>
        <li>• <strong>Path to citizenship:</strong> 5 years continuous residence</li>
        <li>• <strong>Work rights:</strong> Full rights to manage your business</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Why Choose Japan?</h3>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="border border-green-200 bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Advantages</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
          <li>• World's 3rd largest economy</li>
          <li>• Exceptional safety and quality of life</li>
          <li>• Accessible investment threshold (¥5M)</li>
          <li>• Excellent healthcare system</li>
          <li>• Gateway to Asian markets</li>
          <li>• Strong rule of law and IP protection</li>
          <li>• 5-year path to citizenship possible</li>
          <li>• Highly educated workforce</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-amber-200 bg-amber-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">Considerations</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-amber-800">
          <li>• Must actively manage business (not passive)</li>
          <li>• Japanese language important for success</li>
          <li>• Complex business culture and customs</li>
          <li>• Office requirement adds cost</li>
          <li>• 10-year standard path to PR</li>
          <li>• High cost of living (Tokyo especially)</li>
          <li>• Bureaucracy can be challenging</li>
          <li>• Aging population affects labor market</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        <strong>Startup Visa option:</strong> Japan also offers a Startup Visa in designated cities (Tokyo, Fukuoka, etc.) that allows 6-12 months to prepare your business before meeting full Business Manager requirements. This is ideal for entrepreneurs who need time to establish the company, secure office space, and refine their business plan before the formal visa application.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Quick Decision Guide -->
  <section id="quick-decision" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Quick Decision Guide</h2>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Japan's Business Manager Visa is Right For You If:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
          <li>• You want to actively build a business in Asia</li>
          <li>• You're drawn to Japanese culture and lifestyle</li>
          <li>• You value safety and quality of life</li>
          <li>• You have a Japan-relevant business idea</li>
          <li>• You're willing to learn Japanese</li>
          <li>• You have ¥5M+ to invest in a real business</li>
          <li>• You want access to Japanese/Asian markets</li>
          <li>• You appreciate long-term relationship building</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">Consider Other Options If:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-amber-800">
          <li>• You want a passive investment visa</li>
          <li>• You prefer English-only business environment</li>
          <li>• You need fast PR (Japan is 10 years standard)</li>
          <li>• You're not prepared for Japanese business culture</li>
          <li>• You prefer Mediterranean/Western lifestyle</li>
          <li>• You want real estate-based investment visa</li>
          <li>• You prefer lower cost of living</li>
          <li>• You need a home-based business setup</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Japan vs. Other Asian Options</h3>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead class="bg-neutral-100">
          <tr>
            <th class="px-4 py-2 text-left">Country</th>
            <th class="px-4 py-2 text-left">Program</th>
            <th class="px-4 py-2 text-left">Min. Investment</th>
            <th class="px-4 py-2 text-left">PR Timeline</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium">Japan</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">Business Manager Visa</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">¥5,000,000 (~$33K)</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">10 years (1 year HSFP)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-neutral-50">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium">Singapore</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">EntrePass / GIP</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">S$100K / S$10M</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">2 years / immediate</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium">Hong Kong</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">Investment Visa</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">No minimum (viable business)</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">7 years</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-neutral-50">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium">Thailand</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">Thailand Elite / LTR</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">฿600K-2M / income-based</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">No PR path</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        <strong>Why Japan stands out:</strong> Japan offers the lowest investment threshold among major Asian economies for an entrepreneur visa. The ¥5M (~$33K) is far below Singapore's GIP ($10M+) and more accessible than Hong Kong's increasingly complex requirements. Japan also offers a rare path to citizenship (5 years)—impossible in Singapore and very limited in Hong Kong.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Investment Requirements -->
  <section id="investment-requirements" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Investment Requirements</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Japan's Business Manager Visa requires either capital investment of ¥5,000,000 or employment of 2+ full-time Japanese residents. Most foreign entrepreneurs choose the capital route. The investment must be in an actual operating business—you cannot simply deposit money in a bank account.
    </p>

    <ComparisonTable columns={requirementsColumns} rows={requirementsRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">Understanding the ¥5,000,000 Requirement</h3>

    <div class="space-y-6 mb-6">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">What Counts as Investment</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">The ¥5M must be genuinely invested in business operations: company capital, equipment, inventory, office setup, initial operating expenses. Immigration officials will verify that funds were actually used for business purposes, not just temporarily deposited.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Source of Funds</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">You must demonstrate legitimate source of the investment capital. Bank statements, sale of assets, loan agreements, or investor commitments work. Japan is strict about anti-money laundering—expect thorough documentation requirements.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-purple-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Office Requirement</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">You must have a dedicated physical office—home offices don't qualify. The office must be a commercial lease (not residential) with your company name on the mailbox/directory. Shared offices or virtual offices are generally not accepted, though some serviced offices may qualify if they meet specific criteria.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-amber-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Alternative: Employee Route</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Instead of ¥5M capital, you can qualify by employing 2+ full-time employees who are Japanese residents (citizens or permanent residents). This can reduce the capital requirement but adds payroll obligations from day one.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Company Structure Options</h3>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Kabushiki Kaisha (KK / 株式会社)</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
          <li>• Traditional Japanese corporation</li>
          <li>• Higher prestige with Japanese partners</li>
          <li>• Minimum capital: ¥1 (though ¥5M for visa)</li>
          <li>• Registration cost: ~¥200,000</li>
          <li>• Annual compliance requirements</li>
          <li>• Preferred for larger businesses</li>
          <li>• Better for fundraising/investors</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Godo Kaisha (GK / 合同会社)</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
          <li>• Similar to US LLC</li>
          <li>• Lower setup cost: ~¥60,000</li>
          <li>• Simpler administration</li>
          <li>• Flexible profit distribution</li>
          <li>• Less prestigious than KK</li>
          <li>• Popular for small/solo businesses</li>
          <li>• Qualifies for Business Manager Visa</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <p class="text-amber-800">
        <strong>Important:</strong> You must be actively engaged in managing the business—this is not a passive investment visa. Immigration expects to see you making business decisions, meeting with clients, and running operations. Absentee ownership or purely remote management from another country won't satisfy visa requirements.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Insurance Requirements -->
  <section id="insurance-requirements" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Insurance Requirements</h2>

    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-2">National Health Insurance is Mandatory</h3>
      <p class="text-green-800">
        Japan requires all residents to enroll in health insurance. As a business owner, you'll typically join the National Health Insurance (国民健康保険 / Kokumin Kenkō Hoken) system. Enrollment happens at your local city or ward office within 14 days of registering your residence.
      </p>
    </div>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Japan's universal healthcare system provides excellent coverage at 70% of costs (patient pays 30% coinsurance). As a self-employed business owner, you'll be in the NHI system rather than the employee-based Shakai Hoken system. Many expats supplement NHI with private insurance to cover the 30% copay and provide international coverage.
    </p>

    <ComparisonTable columns={insuranceColumns} rows={insuranceRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">Understanding Japanese Health Insurance</h3>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="border border-blue-200 bg-blue-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-3">National Health Insurance (NHI)</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-blue-800">
          <li>• Mandatory for all residents</li>
          <li>• Premium: income + municipality-based</li>
          <li>• Typical: ¥30,000-80,000/month</li>
          <li>• 70% coverage (you pay 30%)</li>
          <li>• All hospitals and clinics accept</li>
          <li>• Includes dental (basic)</li>
          <li>• Limited overseas coverage</li>
          <li>• Must pay even when abroad</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-green-200 bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Private Insurance (Optional)</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
          <li>• Supplements 30% copay</li>
          <li>• International coverage for travel</li>
          <li>• English-speaking support</li>
          <li>• Access to international hospitals</li>
          <li>• Higher limits for serious illness</li>
          <li>• Cancer insurance popular in Japan</li>
          <li>• Medical evacuation coverage</li>
          <li>• Premium: ¥10,000-60,000/month</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Insurance Strategy for Business Owners</h3>

    <div class="space-y-4 mb-6">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Phase 1: Before Arrival</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">For visa application, health insurance proof isn't strictly required but shows financial stability. Consider travel insurance for the initial setup period before NHI enrollment.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Phase 2: After Registration</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Enroll in NHI within 14 days of residence registration. Your premium is calculated based on previous year's income (first year often lower). This is mandatory—you cannot opt out.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-purple-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Phase 3: Long-Term Strategy</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Most business owners maintain NHI (mandatory) plus optional private supplement. Popular additions: cancer insurance (very common in Japan), copay coverage, and international travel insurance for business trips.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        <strong>High-cost illness protection:</strong> Japan's NHI includes a High-Cost Medical Expense Benefit (高額療養費) that caps your monthly out-of-pocket at approximately ¥80,000-150,000 depending on income, even for expensive treatments. This provides excellent catastrophic coverage without private insurance.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Box -->
  <CTABox
    variant="highlight"
    title="Need insurance for your Japan Business Manager Visa?"
    description="Compare international insurers that supplement Japan's NHI system."
    buttonText="Compare Premium Insurance"
    buttonHref="/go/allianz-care"
  />

  <!-- Section: Recommended Providers -->
  <section id="recommended-providers" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Japanese NHI is mandatory and excellent, but many expats add private coverage for international travel, English support, and copay coverage. Here are options for different needs:
    </p>

    <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">Provider Recommendations by Situation</h3>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">NHI-Only (Budget Approach)</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Many long-term residents rely solely on NHI. It's comprehensive, accepted everywhere, and the 30% copay with high-cost caps is manageable. Add travel insurance for international trips. This is the most cost-effective approach for those comfortable with Japanese healthcare.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Frequent International Traveler</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Allianz Care or Cigna Global provide worldwide coverage that complements NHI. Useful for business travelers who need seamless care outside Japan. These also offer English support and international hospital networks.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-purple-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Cancer/Critical Illness Concern</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Japan has high cancer rates, and cancer insurance is extremely popular. AFLAC Japan dominates this market. These policies pay lump sums upon diagnosis, covering lost income and uncovered treatments. Many Japanese consider this essential.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-amber-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Want English-Speaking Full Service</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Tokyo has international hospitals (St. Luke's, Tokyo Midtown) that accept international insurance. Cigna Global or Allianz Care provide direct billing and English coordination. Higher cost but removes language barriers in healthcare.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

