  <!-- Section: Common Mistakes -->
  <section id="mistakes" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Using Home Address or Virtual Office</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Japan requires a dedicated commercial office space. Residential addresses, virtual offices, and mail-forwarding services don't qualify. Invest in proper office space—even a small commercial lease in a co-working building that provides dedicated space may work, but verify with immigration first.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Treating It as Passive Investment</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">This is not a "park money and get residence" visa. You must actively manage the business. Immigration checks that you're genuinely running operations. Being absent from Japan for extended periods or having someone else manage everything risks visa renewal denial.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Insufficient Business Plan</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">A vague "I'll figure it out" approach doesn't work. Present a concrete business plan with: what you'll sell/provide, target customers, revenue model, why Japan specifically, and financial projections. Immigration officers assess business viability.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Banking Challenges</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Opening Japanese bank accounts is notoriously difficult for foreigners. Plan ahead: work with specialists who can help arrange company accounts, expect the process to take time, and have backup payment solutions. Personal accounts may require residence history.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Ignoring Japanese Business Culture</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Japan has distinct business customs: relationship-building takes time, hierarchy matters, indirect communication is common, and punctuality is essential. Foreign entrepreneurs who dismiss these as "old-fashioned" often struggle. Invest in understanding Japanese business culture.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

